Readme

--It is good pracdtise to use this programs with pcbnew closed.
--AFTER USING bloquesgemelos of refergemelas, restart pcbnew


tablareferencias.c  (compiled tablareferencias)
Input File: fileSCH.sch Common file to all twin hierarchical sheets
(Parameter up or down)

Usage: $ ./tablareferencias fileSCH.sch up

Output file: fileSCH-Referencias.csv 
Text file containing all blocks in columns. Each row contains the references of the equivalent footprints

The output file "pruebaslineas" is also generated, though the program doesn't use it. Its only use is to check that all components are sorted by hierarchical sheets.

--Warning: if due to how eeschema works there are more blocks in fileSCH.sch than hierarchical sheets, unused blocks should be deleted from fileSCH-Referencias.csv (columns of fileSCH-Referencias.csv) and cell A1 modified with the actual number of blocks.

--First column must be the already placed block in pcbnew.
--The rest of the columns can be sorted (if desired) in the way the user needs.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
		
bloquesgemelos.c (compiled bloquesgemelos)
Input File 1: filePCB.kicad_pcb
Input File 2: fileSCH-Referencias.csv generated by generaref.c

Input parameter 3: distance x (in mm) from a footprint in a block and its equivalent footprint of the next block
Input parameter 4: distance y (in mm) from a footprint in a block and its equivalent footprint of the next block

Usage: $ ./bloquesgemelos filePCB.kicad_pcb fileSCH-Referencias.csv 50 0
will place all the blocks in the same y coordinate with a distance of 50 mm from twin (equivalent) footprints.

Usually x or y parameter will be zero.

Output file 1: input file renamed as filePCB.kicad_pcbold
Output file 2: Output file renamed after the original input file -> filePCB.kicad_pcb
Output file 3: fileSCH-Bloques.csv  File with absolute footprint coordinates:   ref posx posy angle

Output file 3 is only used for information.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

refergemelas.c (compiled refergemelas)
Input File 1: filePCB.kicad_pcb
Input File 2: fileSCH-Referencias.csv generated by generaref.c

Usasge: $ ./refergemelas filePCB.kicad_pcb fileSCH-Referencias.csv

Output file 1: input file renamed as filePCB.kicad_pcbold
Output file 2: Output file renamed after the original input file -> filePCB.kicad_pcb
Output file 3: fileSCH-Relativas.csv  File with the related positions of the footprint references: ref posx posy angle 

Output file 3 is only used for information.

In the new filePCB.kicad_pcb references are placed as those of the first block.



		